uo;s with you to tell them.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re able to tell someone in the UK you&rsquo;ve been detained, they can call the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (<abbr title=\"Foreign and Commonwealth Office\">FCO</abbr>) in London, which runs the consular service. </p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Foreign and Commonwealth Office</strong>  </p>\n\n<p>From outside the UK: +44 (0)207 008 1500<br />\nOpen 24 hours</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Consular staff will try to contact you within 24 hours of being told of your arrest and if you want they will try to visit you as soon as possible.</p>\n\n<p>The British Consul can tell your family or friends that you&rsquo;ve been arrested or detained, if you want them to.</p>\n\n<h2>Who can get help</h2>\n\n<p>You can get support abroad if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>you’re a British national (have the right to live permanently in the UK and can enter or leave as you wish)</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>you have dual British nationality but aren&rsquo;t in the country of your other nationality</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Who can&rsquo;t get help</h2>\n\n<p>If you have dual British nationality and are in the country of your other nationality, you won&rsquo;t usually get support. Exceptions may be made for humanitarian reasons. </p>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Your rights and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Frights.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes being arrested, cautions, discrimination and consumer rights","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Frights","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/rights"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal processes, courts and the police","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=jus