li>pass your complaint on to another public body, if appropriate - tell them if you don&rsquo;t want them to do this</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If they find anything wrong and have enough evidence, they may ask a court to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>close the company down</li>\n  <li>disqualify the company’s directors</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If they find an offence may have been committed, they&rsquo;ll send a report to the appropriate authority, who will decide whether to carry out a criminal investigation. </p>\n\n<h3>What can&rsquo;t be investigated</h3>\n\n<p>The Insolvency Service won&rsquo;t usually investigate complaints where:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>there&rsquo;s no public interest (eg an internal company dispute)</li>\n  <li>an investigation by somebody else is already underway</li>\n  <li>the main issue is that the company isn&rsquo;t paying its debts</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>How to complain</h3>\n\n<p>Get more information or report misconduct using the Insolvency Service’s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.bis.gov.uk/insolvency/Companies/investigations-hotline\" title=\"Investigations Hotline\">investigations hotline.</a></p>\n\n<p>You can also write to them:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nIntelligence Hub\n<br />Investigations and Enforcement Services\n<br />Insolvency Service\n<br />3rd Floor Cannon House\n<br />18 Priory Queensway\n<br />Birmingham\n<br />B4 6FD\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Give as much information as you can when you complain.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Complain to Companies House</h2>\n\n<p>Companies House deals with complaints about companies that fail to file documents such as annual accounts or returns, or file fraudulent documents.</p>\n\n<p>If you suspect a company of breaking the law on the filing of documents, email the details to <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#102;&#114;&#097;&#117;&#100;&#064;&#099;&#111;&#109;&#112;&#097;&#110;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#104;&#111;&#11